title: Baroque and Rococo in Latin America (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Baroque and Rococo in Latin America
Dover Publications | 1967 | ISBN: N/A | English | 324 pages | PDF | 55.7 MB

Until very recently, colonial art and architecture in Latin America has been a greatly neglected and underestimated phenomenon. All too often it has been misunderstood as an empty imitation of European forms, debased by intellectual poverty. One of the books which led to an appreciation of the grandeur and beauty of this colonial art, as well as to an understanding of its complex history, was this book, by the renowned art historian Pal Kelemen
